Open Powershell.
1. Install Docker
$ dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart

2. Activate VirtualMachinePlatform
$ dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart

3. Download nad Install Linux Kernel Update Package
https://learn.microsoft.com/ko-kr/windows/wsl/install-manual

4. Set wsl2 as default version
$ wsl --set-default-version 2

5. Go to Microsoft Store & Install Ubuntu

6. check wsl version
$ wsl -l -v

7. Change it to version 2 if it's version 1. 
$ wsl --set-version Ubuntu 2

8. Install Docker
https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop
